In the first half of 2020, I developed an application consisting of the following parts:
- database PostgreSQL;
- server part on Java;
- web interface.
The database stores information about users (name, login, password, date of birth, date of employment, individual tax number, salary) in one table and another table stores information about user contacts (mobile number, email). These tables are linked by a key.
The web interface allows you to perform the following actions:
- view all user data in a table and see in a separate column how many full years the user is at the moment;
- according to the filter, which specifies an integer, all data of users who have worked so far less than the entered number are displayed in the form of a table;
- create a new employee;
- remove an employee;
- edit the data of any employee;
- export a table with the data of all employees to an Excel document.
When creating a new employee or editing the data of an existing employee, the information entered by the user is validated.
This application is developed on the basis of the following technologies:
- servlets;
- JDBC;
- html, css.
https://github.com/SinchukAlexandr/java_ee_db

In the second half of 2020, I completely rewrote this application while maintaining the functionality using the following technologies:
- Spring Framework;
- web MVC;
- JDBC Template;
- html, css.
https://github.com/SinchukAlexandr/Java-EE-db-1.3
